Meeting a number of Premium Grade building standards, 15 William Street is an outstanding A Grade Melbourne CBD building with highly efficient Docklands style floor plates (2,000sqm +per floor). 

With the CBD rapidly shifting towards the William Street and Collins Street juncture, 15 William Street sits among some of Melbourne's landmark buildings including The Rialto Towers and will put your business right in the thick of the action.

15 William Street is a 20 story office building which in 2003 went through a comprehensive redevelopment worth in excess of $100 million. This redevelopment included significant upgrades to building services elevating these to Premium grade standard, plus additional car parking on Flinders Street. In 2006, four levels were added to the Flinders Street extension for use as a Child Care Centre plus additional car parking. In 2015, a first class new end-of-trip facility opened in the basement of the building.

The hotel style ground floor lobby offers occupants and visitors a classic, modern and comfortable feel, with various casual meeting spaces.

15 William Street is predominantly an island site and occupants benefit from excellent natural light on all four sides with the southern side of the floor benefiting from a Yarra River, Southbank and Crown Casino outlook.

15 William Street features:

- Excellent natural light to all sides
- Large efficient floor plates with contiguous options available
- Both fully refurbished and fitted options available
- High quality end-of-trip facilities featuring 21 showers, 430 lockers, secure bicycle parking for 251 bikes, complimentary towel service, drying cupboards, bike maintenance facilities and a bike accessory vending machine.
- Onsite security and concierge service
- Abundant car parking available (generous allocation ratio of 1 bay per 110sqm of lettable area) plus public car parking for visitors via the onsite operator Secure Parking
- Strong environmental credentials with a 5.5 Star NABERS Energy Rating 
- Onsite Child Care Centre, offering unparalleled convenience to occupants
- Short walk to Flinders Street and Southern Cross Stations and adjacent Flinders Street, William Street and Collins Street trams

287 Collins Street is situated on one of Melbourne’s most prominent corners and is a historic landmark within the CBD. Benefiting from the prestige of Collins Street and the everyday convenience of Elizabeth Street, this is a rare opportunity to secure office space in a beautiful heritage listed building.

Designed by Stephenson & Turner, this 9-level building – known as Royal Bank Chambers has recently undergone on-floor refurbishments offering creative, fully fitted whole floors. 

Brand new high quality end of trip facilities being delivered in 2021 on level 1 including bike racks, lockers and showers. 

With its prime position in the heart of the CBD, 287 Collins Street is well connected to metropolitan Melbourne and greater Victoria. No matter how you commute to work – be it via train, tram, bus or soon-to-be Metro rail – stations and stops are just footsteps away. Cycling to the office has never been easier with quick access to on and off-road routes, including the Yarra Trail and Capital City Trail.

215 Franklin Street is an impressive stand alone commercial office building which benefits from an accessible and functional location surrounded by public transport options and amenity such as the Queen Victoria Market.

Situated at the Northern precinct of the CBD, 215 Franklin Street is well serviced by public transport and vehicles. Both Melbourne Central Train Station and Flagstaff Train Station are only a few minutes’ walk from the building, with ample car parking across the road at Queen Victoria Market as well as a number of commercial car parks within a block.

The building is fitted with classrooms, lecture theaters, staff rooms and breakout areas for both staff and students.

Approximate area of 2,500sqm becoming available.

- Superior accessibility to public transport; Parliament Railway Station and Flinders Street Station within easy walking distance, Collins and Flinders Street trams, and bus services operating along Exhibition Street.
 
- Outstanding access to Citylink via the Exhibition Street extension.
 
- 5 Star hotel style Concierge Service located on the ground floor, Exhibition Street entrance, and is manned from 8.00am to 6.00pm Monday to Friday.
